Vintage illustration of three ancient stone tablets standing in a desert landscape at sunset, each tablet carved with different intricate geometric patterns representing data hierarchies—the first tablet weathered and monolithic with rigid grid-like etchings, the second featuring flowing tree-branch patterns with nested loops, the third sleek and minimal with curved bracket-shaped carvings. The tablets are arranged in a timeline formation from left to right, progressively becoming more refined and elegant. Warm amber and ochre tones dominate the scene, with long dramatic shadows stretching across rippled sand dunes. A single archaeologist figure in 1920s expedition attire stands small in the distance, examining the progression. The sky transitions from deep orange to dusty purple, with wispy clouds catching the last light.
